addLiquidity(address,address,uint256,uin.details: Make sure to approve the tokens to be transferred by this contract before invoking. Steps: 1. Identifies the pool index based on the token pair. 2. Distributes tokens to liquidity clusters. 3. Mints LP tokens in a manner proportional to the added liquidity. Reverts if: - The pool for the token pair does not exist. - The amount to be minted falls below the minimum liquidity threshold. Emits: - LiquidityAdded event with details of the liquidity addition.

params.provider: The address that will receive the minted LP tokens.
params.thatAmount: The amount of thatToken to add to the liquidity pool.
params.thatToken: The other token in the liquidity pool pair.
params.thisAmount: The amount of thisToken to add to the liquidity pool.
params.thisToken: A token in the liquidity pool pair.

params._thatToken: The other token of the LP token pair.
params._thisToken: A token of the LP token pair.

returns._0: newLpToken The address of the newly created LP token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

redeemLiquidity(address,uint256,address).details: This function burns LP tokens and transfers the corresponding underlying assets to the recipient. Steps: 1. Validate the amount of LP tokens to be redeemed. 2. Identify the pool index using the tokens in the LP token. 3. Calculate the redeemable amount of each underlying asset. 4. Burn the provided amount of LP tokens. 5. Transfer the underlying assets to the recipient. Reverts if: - The specified amount of LP tokens is zero. - The specified amount of LP tokens exceeds the contract's balance. Emits: - LiquidityRedeemed event with details of the redemption.

params.lpToken: The LP token to be redeemed.
params.lpTokenAmount: The amount of LP tokens to redeem.
params.recipient: The address to receive the redeemed underlying assets.

returns.thatOut: The redeemed amount of the second underlying asset.
returns.thisOut: The redeemed amount of the first underlying asset.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._liquidityManager: The address of the LiquidityManager contract.

params._poolManager: The address of the PoolManager contract.

params._swapManager: The address of the SwapManager contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addLiquidity(address,address,uint256,uin.notice: Adds liquidity to the pool of a token pair.

redeemLiquidity(address,uint256,address).notice: Redeems LP tokens to withdraw underlying assets from the liquidity pool.
